info.title: Rock and Fluid Sample DDMS
info.description: OSDU Rock and Fluid Sample DDMS

get.description: Endpoint that serves Prometheus metrics.

Get the bulk data for a given `RockSampleAnalysis` object by record id.

Use the `Accept` request header to specify response format (`application/json` and `application/parquet` are supported).

The `columns_filter`, `rows_filter`, and `columns_aggregation` query parameters can be used to manage data in response.

Required roles: `users.datalake.viewers` or `users.datalake.editors` or `users.datalake.admins`.
In addition, users must be members of a data group(ACL) to access the data.

parameters.description: Specifies the proper data partition id

schema.title: data-partition-id
schema.description: Specifies the proper data partition id

parameters.name: data-partition-id

post.description:
Upload the bulk data for a given `RockSampleAnalysis` object by record id.
It creates a new version of the record.
The previous meta-data with bulk data is available by their `versions`.

Use the `Content-Type` request header to specify payload format (`application/json` and `application/parquet` are supported).
Use the `Accept` request header to specify response format (`application/json` and `application/parquet` are supported).

Required roles: `users.datalake.editors` or `users.datalake.admins`.
In addition, users must be members of a data group(ACL) to access the data.

get.description:
Get the source report file for a given `RockSampleAnalysis` object by record id.

Datasets identifiers from the `Datasets` record's property are used as source file references. If the record relates to multiple reports, the reports' source files will be zipped.

Required roles: `users.datalake.viewers` or `users.datalake.editors` or `users.datalake.admins`.
In addition, users must be members of a data group(ACL) to access the data.
